                                    The major design of the city was mapped out by the French architect Le Corbusier.
                                </li>
                                <li>
                                    Chandigarh was the first planned city in India and it was the dream city of the first Prime Minister Jawaharlal Nehru.
                                </li>
                                <li>
                                    The cities of Chandigarh, Panchkula (Haryana) and Mohali (Punjab) are together known as 'Tricity'.
                                </li>
                                <li>
                                    Chandigarh is said to have a number of roundabouts which help in easy flow of traffic. These roundabouts also provide a beauty to the city.
                                </li>
                            </ul>
                        </p>
